Sweet Andi got tubes in her ears today. She did amazing and we are so thankful for the awesome team at @bostonchildrens hospital. On Andi’s second day of life she failed her newborn hearing test. We figured this was a build of fluid in her ears and booked our next appointment to have a more intense hearing test. She did great during that test - if you’ve done this one you know how hard it is. The baby has to be asleep on your lap for about an hour while certain pitches are played in their ears - she passed! At the next follow up exam she did awesome and her hearing had improved! She still had fluid in her ears, but it wasn’t stopping her. Then the ear infections began - 3 in 3 months and we also learned about her allergy to amoxicillin. At her next hearing test we met with her ENT and he recommended the tubes procedure and convinced us that she was a great candidate for it. So here we are today. These will stay in for about a year give or take! Fingers crossed no more ear infections!

The twins love this pumpkin egg bake and SO DO I because it’s the easiest thing to bake ever. Huge thank you to @the_laura_young for sharing many many months ago! Here’s the deets:
8 eggs
1 can of pumpkin puree
1/4 cup milk
1 tbsp vanilla extract
1/4 tsp nutmeg 
1/4 tsp cinnamon 
Combine in a mixing bowl and pour into a greased baking dish (I use a 7x11 or 2 qt baking dish)
Bake at 375 for 25-32 min until squishy in the middle 
The best part is that we serve it cold in the AM 
ENJOY! 🎃

If you’re in Orlando @peppapigthemeparkflorida is a must! Our kids loved it and so did I! 
1. It’s great for kids of all ages! Check the height requirements for rides. Most of the rides are ok for all ages but there were a few that were 34+ inches to ride (the twins just barely too short)
2. It was SO clean and felt brand new even though it opened in 2022. 
3. There’s only one restaurant but the food is actually pretty good!
4. There’s a huge splash pad and it was even open in January. 
5. I would definitely go back! Look into the annual pass option if you’re a local 🐷
